author: Seattle Times staff
title: Reign FC defender Cox will retire at 29
text:
Reign FC defender Cox will retire at 29 Originally published October 19, 2015 at 9:22 pm Seattle Reign FC and former U.S. women’s national team defender Stephanie Cox announced her retirement from professional soccer Monday. By Seattle Times staff The Seattle Times 
Seattle Reign FC and former U.S. women’s national team defender Stephanie Cox announced her retirement from professional soccer Monday. 
Cox, 29, made 49 appearances in 2½ seasons with Reign FC. 
The Elk Grove, Calif., native began playing for the U.S. national team in 2006 and amassed 89 career caps, winning a gold medal in the 2008 Olympics in China. Volleyball 
Washington sits at No. 4 in the national coaches poll, marking 200 consecutive appearances in the top 25 dating to 2003. The Huskies have been in the top 10 in 176 of the 200 polls. Washington (17-1, 7-1 Pac-12) plays at Stanford on Wednesday night. Most Read Stories 
• Western Washington middle blocker Kayleigh Harper was named the Great Northwest Athletic Conference defensive player of the week. Women’s soccer 
Western Washington goalie Ashley Haden was named GNAC defensive player of the week. Men’s soccer 
Shane Haworth from Seattle University was named Western Athletic Conference defensive player of the week. Women’s golf 
Washington is seventh at the Stanford Intercollegiate with a 15-over 583. Ying Luo (73) and Wenyung Keh (70) are tied for 13th. Men’s golf 
Seattle University (14-under 562) is in second place after two rounds of the Bill Cullum Invitational in Simi Valley, Calif. Joe Harvie (68, 66) is the leader at 10 under. 
• Western Washington (593) is eighth at the Otter Invitational in Seaside, Calif. Brett Johnson (69, 74) is tied for 11th at 1-under 143. Men’s rowing 
Washington’s varsity eight was fourth on the last day of the Head of the Charles regatta in Cambridge, Mass. The Huskies had no holdovers from the varsity eight that competed at the IRA national championships in June. From sports-information reports.
